																				<article class="col insidepagethumbholder rotator ">
								<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/features/dammed-but-not-doomed/" class="tagmanager" id="Related_article_44907" >
								<img width="900" height="432" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-skutik-dam.jpg" class="insidepagethumb wp-post-image" alt="alewives" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-skutik-dam.jpg 2000w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-skutik-dam-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-skutik-dam-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-skutik-dam-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-skutik-dam-1536x737.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-skutik-dam-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" />								<header class="insidepagethumbinfo">
									<h2>Dammed but Not Doomed</h2>
									<h3>As dams come down on the Skutik River, the once-demonized alewife—a fish beloved by the Passamaquoddy—gets a second chance at life.</h3>
									<p class="insidepagethumbinfodate">Mar 5, 2024 | 3,600 words, about 18 minutes</p>
								</header>
								</a>
							</article>
																				<article class="col insidepagethumbholder rotator ">
								<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/features/fish-below-your-feet-and-other-solutions-for-a-living-harbor/" class="tagmanager" id="Related_article_27176" >
								<img width="900" height="432" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-eco-engineering.jpg" class="insidepagethumb wp-post-image" alt="illustration of sea life at Seattle&#039;s waterfront" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-eco-engineering.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-eco-engineering-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-eco-engineering-2048x984.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-eco-engineering-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-eco-engineering-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-eco-engineering-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-eco-engineering-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" />								<header class="insidepagethumbinfo">
									<h2>Fish Below Your Feet and Other Solutions for a Living Harbor</h2>
									<h3>In Seattle, Singapore, and other waterfront cities around the world, engineers are creating life-enhancing designs to encourage marine biodiversity.</h3>
									<p class="insidepagethumbinfodate">May 14, 2019 | 4,000 words, about 20 minutes</p>
								</header>
								</a>
